All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Appointment
    The Appointment class simulates an Appointment.
    appointmentAddController
    The appointmentAddController is used as the Controller for appointmentAddForm.fxml.
    AppointmentDao
    AppointmentDao is the Interface for AppointmentImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    AppointmentImp
    AppointmentImp implements AppointmentDao and holds methods to perform CRUD operations on appointments in the database.
    appointmentModifyController
    The appointmentModifyController is used as the Controller for appointmentModifyForm.fxml.
    Contact
    The Contact class simulates a Contact.
    ContactDao
    ContactDao is the Interface for ContactImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    ContactImp
    ContactImp implements ContactDao and holds methods to perform CRUD operations on contacts in the database.
    Country
    The Country class simulates a Country.
    CountryDao
    CountryDao is the Interface for CountryImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    CountryDivCount
    The CountryDivCount class is used to hold data for each row in the main form 'Number of Customers by Country and Division' Table.
    CountryDivCountDao
    CountryDivCountDao is the Interface for CountryDivCountImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    CountryDivCountImp
    CountryDivCountImp implements CountryDivCountDao and holds a method to gather a count of customers in each division for a given country for use in the main form 'Number of Customers by Country and Division' Table.
    CountryImp
    CountryImp implements CountryDao and holds methods to perform CRUD operations on countries in the database.
    Customer
    The Customer class simulates a Customer.
    customerAddController
    The customerAddController is used as the Controller for customerAddForm.fxml.
    CustomerDao
    CustomerDao is the Interface for CustomerImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    CustomerImp
    CustomerImp implements CustomerDao and holds methods to perform CRUD operations on customers in the database.
    customerModifyController
    The customerModifyController is used as the Controller for customerModifyForm.fxml.
    DBConnection
    The DBConnection class is used to create a connection to the database.
    DBQuery
    The DBQuery class is used to create a Statement for querying the database.
    Division
    The Division class simulates a First-Level Division.
    DivisionDao
    DivisionDao is the Interface for DivisionImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    DivisionImp
    DivisionImp implements DivisionDao and holds methods to perform CRUD operations on divisions in the database.
    FileOutputInterface
    FileOutputInterface is used for outputting to a file.
    loginFormController
    The loginFormController is used as the Controller for loginForm.fxml.
    Main
    The Main class is used to launch the program and open the loginForm.fxml first.
    mainFormController
    The mainFormController is used as the Controller for mainForm.fxml.
    MonthTypeCount
    The MonthTypeCount class is used to hold data for each row in the main form 'Number of Appointments by Type and Month in the Current Year' Table.
    MonthTypeCountDao
    MonthTypeCountDao is the Interface for MonthTypeCountImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    MonthTypeCountImp
    MonthTypeCountImp implements MonthTypeCountDao and holds a method to gather a count of appointments by types for each month for use in the main form 'Number of Appointments by Type and Month in the Current Year' Table.
    TimeListsInterface
    TimeListsInterface is used for returning a list of Strings to indicate time.
    TimeMethods
    The TimeMethods class holds utility methods related to time used throughout the application.
    User
    The User class simulates a User.
    UserDao
    UserDao is the Interface for UserImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    UserImp
    UserImp implements UserDao and holds methods to perform CRUD operations on users in the databse.
    _AppComboDao
    _AppComboDao is the Interface for _AppComboImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    _AppComboImp
    _AppComboImp implements _AppComboDao and holds methods to gather Appointments to display in the main form Appointments Table.
    _AppContactCustCombo
    The _AppContactCustCombo class holds a combination of Appointment, Contact, Customer, and User objects and is used in the main form Appointments Table and for sending data to appointmentModifyController.
    _CustComboDao
    _CustComboDao is the Interface for _CustComboImp to ensure it uses all of these methods with appropriate returns and parameters.
    _CustComboImp
    _CustComboImp implements _CustComboDao and holds a method to gather Customers to display in the main form Customers Table.
    _CustDivCountryCombo
    The _CustDivCountryCombo class holds a combination of Customer, Division, and Country objects and is used in the main form Customers Table and for sending data to customerModifyController.
